1
00:00:21,550 --> 00:00:22,120
Is it out?

2
00:00:23,620 --> 00:00:24,340
[IELTS Exam]

3
00:00:23,920 --> 00:00:24,420
What score?

4
00:00:24,370 --> 00:00:25,570
[Total score 6]

5
00:00:25,760 --> 00:00:26,830
Bowen, I got a six.

6
00:00:30,160 --> 00:00:30,710
A six?

7
00:00:32,880 --> 00:00:34,390
Are you sure you didn't miss a zero?

8
00:00:34,390 --> 00:00:35,390
No, it's six.

9
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:37,000
Even if I just guessed,

10
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:38,200
I could get over 10 points.

11
00:00:38,200 --> 00:00:39,860
How could you only score a six?

12
00:00:41,120 --> 00:00:41,840
You've disgraced Mom's status

13
00:00:41,840 --> 00:00:43,200
as an English teacher.

14
00:00:43,280 --> 00:00:43,680
Bowen—

15
00:00:43,750 --> 00:00:44,880
Come over here.

16
00:00:49,110 --> 00:00:49,550
Dad,

17
00:00:50,150 --> 00:00:50,520
Mom,

18
00:00:51,390 --> 00:00:52,390
I have failed you.

19
00:00:53,200 --> 00:00:53,960
I failed to fulfill

20
00:00:53,960 --> 00:00:55,290
the mission you gave me.

21
00:00:56,330 --> 00:00:57,220
I let you down.

22
00:00:57,520 --> 00:00:57,920
Bowen—

23
00:00:57,960 --> 00:00:58,470
Shut up!

24
00:00:59,150 --> 00:00:59,710
Have you forgotten

25
00:00:59,710 --> 00:01:00,520
why Mom

26
00:01:00,520 --> 00:01:01,390
named us Lang Bowen

27
00:01:01,390 --> 00:01:02,190
and Lang Botu?

28
00:01:02,430 --> 00:01:03,470
I haven't forgotten.

29
00:01:03,470 --> 00:01:03,960
Say it.

30
00:01:05,200 --> 00:01:05,940
Number one,

31
00:01:06,040 --> 00:01:06,700
number two.

32
00:01:06,760 --> 00:01:07,400
Louder!

33
00:01:08,760 --> 00:01:09,420
Number one!

34
00:01:09,590 --> 00:01:10,360
Number two!

35
00:01:11,120 --> 00:01:12,000
Mom had such high

36
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:13,600
expectations for us.

37
00:01:15,150 --> 00:01:15,840
Number one,

38
00:01:16,120 --> 00:01:16,789
number two.

39
00:01:17,920 --> 00:01:19,070
If we had a sister...

40
00:01:19,150 --> 00:01:20,789
She would be named Number Three.

41
00:01:20,789 --> 00:01:21,190
Right.

42
00:01:21,480 --> 00:01:23,610
Translated, that would be Lang Bocui.

43
00:01:25,200 --> 00:01:27,230
I'm a failure, not cut out for school,

44
00:01:27,230 --> 00:01:28,840
and unworthy of the title "number one."

45
00:01:28,840 --> 00:01:30,300
Did your genes mutate too?

46
00:01:31,640 --> 00:01:32,200
A six.

47
00:01:33,400 --> 00:01:34,759
Aren't you ashamed?

48
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:37,150
You're still laughing?

49
00:01:37,150 --> 00:01:38,150
Get on your knees!

50
00:01:39,920 --> 00:01:40,350
Kneel.

51
00:01:45,350 --> 00:01:45,789
Mom,

52
00:01:46,870 --> 00:01:48,120
I have good news.

53
00:01:48,759 --> 00:01:50,160
I scored a six on my IELTS.

54
00:01:50,680 --> 00:01:52,310
I can go abroad for grad school.

55
00:01:52,310 --> 00:01:53,440
Who are you kidding?

56
00:01:56,350 --> 00:01:56,759
Mom,

57
00:01:57,680 --> 00:01:59,080
I didn't mean it that way.

58
00:01:59,710 --> 00:02:00,910
He just made me so mad.

59
00:02:02,560 --> 00:02:04,090
I'm telling you, Lang Botu.

60
00:02:04,310 --> 00:02:05,170
You can fool me,

61
00:02:05,870 --> 00:02:06,840
but if you lie to Mom,

62
00:02:06,840 --> 00:02:08,240
believe it or not, I'll kick you to death.

63
00:02:08,240 --> 00:02:08,630
Bowen,

64
00:02:08,630 --> 00:02:10,520
how would I dare lie to Mom?

65
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:12,000
I really passed.

66
00:02:12,670 --> 00:02:13,840
For the IELTS,

67
00:02:13,840 --> 00:02:14,840
a perfect score is nine.

68
00:02:14,840 --> 00:02:15,560
With a six,

69
00:02:15,560 --> 00:02:17,290
I can go abroad for grad school.

70
00:02:19,430 --> 00:02:20,690
You aren't fooling me?

71
00:02:20,840 --> 00:02:22,280
I'm really not.

72
00:02:24,680 --> 00:02:25,940
You scared me to death.

73
00:02:26,560 --> 00:02:27,870
Can you be gentler?

74
00:02:27,870 --> 00:02:29,750
Who designed this scoring system?

75
00:02:29,750 --> 00:02:30,800
So messed up.

76
00:02:33,079 --> 00:02:34,240
Mom, Dad,

77
00:02:34,840 --> 00:02:35,400
Yangyang

78
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:38,150
can apply to foreign universities now.

79
00:02:38,150 --> 00:02:39,410
Your spirits in heaven

80
00:02:39,520 --> 00:02:40,520
can rest in peace.

81
00:04:01,890 --> 00:04:05,640
[Born with Luck]

82
00:04:05,730 --> 00:04:08,720
[Episode 11]

83
00:04:26,680 --> 00:04:27,480
You should go.

84
00:04:27,750 --> 00:04:28,810
He'll be back soon.

85
00:04:30,040 --> 00:04:30,570
Then I...

86
00:04:32,560 --> 00:04:33,890
I'm leaving then, Ying.

87
00:05:58,600 --> 00:05:59,070
Hey,

88
00:05:59,510 --> 00:06:00,440
why are you here?

89
00:06:01,870 --> 00:06:02,730
I just got here.

90
00:06:02,920 --> 00:06:03,780
Looking for me?

91
00:06:04,870 --> 00:06:05,800
Need something?

92
00:06:06,480 --> 00:06:07,080
Of course.

93
00:06:07,430 --> 00:06:08,510
I want to get a drink with you.

94
00:06:08,510 --> 00:06:09,240
If you wanted to drink,

95
00:06:09,240 --> 00:06:10,700
you could've just called.

96
00:06:11,120 --> 00:06:12,920
Why did you come all the way here?

97
00:06:14,630 --> 00:06:16,310
I just wanted to come in person,

98
00:06:16,310 --> 00:06:17,240
so I didn't call.

99
00:06:19,070 --> 00:06:20,600
Look at how guilty you're acting.

100
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:21,310
Are you hiding

101
00:06:21,310 --> 00:06:22,370
something from me?

102
00:06:27,560 --> 00:06:28,190
Me?

103
00:06:30,240 --> 00:06:31,500
I just had to come over.

104
00:06:32,240 --> 00:06:32,950
Why?

105
00:06:36,830 --> 00:06:37,720
We are bros.

106
00:06:37,720 --> 00:06:39,780
Can't you just give it to me straight?

107
00:06:44,870 --> 00:06:45,360
Kai,

108
00:06:50,159 --> 00:06:50,820
I want to...

109
00:06:54,390 --> 00:06:55,650
I'm giving this to you.

110
00:06:58,240 --> 00:06:59,100
What happened?

111
00:07:00,360 --> 00:07:01,690
I loaned out some money.

112
00:07:03,240 --> 00:07:05,240
I'm collecting the debt these days.

113
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:07,460
The guy is a tough nut to crack.

114
00:07:09,190 --> 00:07:10,990
If I come back in a couple of days,

115
00:07:11,310 --> 00:07:12,710
you can give it back to me.

116
00:07:13,720 --> 00:07:14,920
If I don't come back,

117
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:17,930
the car is yours.

118
00:07:22,950 --> 00:07:23,680
Who are they?

119
00:07:23,950 --> 00:07:24,880
I'll go with you.

120
00:07:31,950 --> 00:07:33,080
It's too dangerous.

121
00:07:34,560 --> 00:07:35,560
I'll do it myself.

122
00:07:41,870 --> 00:07:42,390
Bro...

123
00:07:42,750 --> 00:07:43,950
It's very dangerous!

124
00:07:54,480 --> 00:07:55,280
He's so loyal.

125
00:07:56,800 --> 00:07:58,000
I've always wanted to drive it.

126
00:07:58,000 --> 00:07:59,600
Let's take it for a spin. Go!

127
00:08:19,240 --> 00:08:20,900
There is a theory in economics

128
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:23,270
that a person will encounter at least

129
00:08:23,270 --> 00:08:25,190
three major opportunities in life.

130
00:08:25,190 --> 00:08:26,480
If you grasp just one,

131
00:08:27,120 --> 00:08:30,180
you can turn your life around
and cross social classes.

132
00:08:30,680 --> 00:08:31,800
Most people spend their whole lives

133
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:33,150
without grasping even one.

134
00:08:33,150 --> 00:08:33,720
Why?

135
00:08:35,510 --> 00:08:37,240
Because they are not prepared.

136
00:08:38,030 --> 00:08:40,240
They don't realize
when an opportunity comes.

137
00:08:40,240 --> 00:08:41,270
Looking back, they realize

138
00:08:41,270 --> 00:08:43,320
that it slipped through their fingers.

139
00:08:43,320 --> 00:08:44,630
Opportunities are always left for

140
00:08:44,630 --> 00:08:45,960
those who are prepared.

141
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:48,760
Looking back at my past decades,

142
00:08:49,360 --> 00:08:51,960
I've already missed
my first big opportunity.

143
00:08:52,790 --> 00:08:54,550
I didn't do well
in the college entrance exam,

144
00:08:54,550 --> 00:08:57,150
so I planned to study abroad
to improve my resume.

145
00:08:57,150 --> 00:08:58,960
My family sold our house back then

146
00:08:58,960 --> 00:09:02,420
and scraped together hundreds of thousands
to send me abroad.

147
00:09:02,840 --> 00:09:04,670
If we had kept that house until now,

148
00:09:04,670 --> 00:09:06,600
we would've received
demolition compensation

149
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:08,260
and be worth over ten million.

150
00:09:08,270 --> 00:09:09,930
I wouldn't need to do this job.

151
00:09:10,960 --> 00:09:12,960
But there's no point in regretting.

152
00:09:13,320 --> 00:09:15,030
People have to look forward.

153
00:09:15,670 --> 00:09:16,960
Now, the second big opportunity

154
00:09:16,960 --> 00:09:18,200
of this lifetime,

155
00:09:18,960 --> 00:09:21,160
Zhou Rong, this big fish, has swum over.

156
00:09:22,480 --> 00:09:24,360
We must be fully prepared.

157
00:09:25,240 --> 00:09:26,750
We absolutely cannot let this one

158
00:09:26,750 --> 00:09:28,240
slip through our fingers again.

159
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:28,720
Chao,

160
00:09:29,240 --> 00:09:31,440
it's not about slipping through
our fingers now.

161
00:09:31,440 --> 00:09:32,970
If he really comes head-on,

162
00:09:33,150 --> 00:09:34,390
we could stop him.

163
00:09:34,870 --> 00:09:36,320
The problem now

164
00:09:36,790 --> 00:09:38,270
is that he's ahead of us,

165
00:09:38,270 --> 00:09:39,670
and we can't catch up.

166
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:41,270
What's the rush?

167
00:09:41,510 --> 00:09:42,720
There's always a way.

168
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:48,270
We need to get a good car.

169
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:06,870
So annoying.

170
00:10:12,960 --> 00:10:13,910
No manners.

171
00:10:15,080 --> 00:10:16,070
What the hell?

172
00:10:40,670 --> 00:10:41,630
Do you know how to drive?

173
00:10:41,630 --> 00:10:42,600
Are you blind?

174
00:10:45,360 --> 00:10:46,600
Bastards.

175
00:10:46,960 --> 00:10:48,560
Get out of the car if you dare.

176
00:11:03,510 --> 00:11:04,750
♪ Ha ha ha ha ♪

177
00:11:07,240 --> 00:11:07,670
Chao,

178
00:11:08,270 --> 00:11:09,670
this jerk is relentless.

179
00:11:08,430 --> 00:11:09,270
♪ Ha ha ha ha ♪

180
00:11:09,840 --> 00:11:10,840
I told you not to cause trouble.

181
00:11:10,840 --> 00:11:12,100
We have a gun in the car.

182
00:11:12,200 --> 00:11:13,000
If we cause a scene

183
00:11:12,710 --> 00:11:13,690
♪ Ha ha ha ha ♪

184
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:13,720
and attract the cops,

185
00:11:13,720 --> 00:11:15,180
we'll go straight to jail.

186
00:11:18,040 --> 00:11:22,250
♪ The sacred light is reborn ♪

187
00:11:23,370 --> 00:11:26,900
♪ The dream of every machine ♪

188
00:11:24,360 --> 00:11:24,790
Stop the car!

189
00:11:24,790 --> 00:11:26,360
Brake!

190
00:11:27,720 --> 00:11:31,550
♪ Foolishness spreads in the revelry ♪

191
00:11:32,550 --> 00:11:33,960
♪ This is humanity ♪

192
00:11:34,450 --> 00:11:36,090
♪ This is humanity ♪

193
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:52,480
Chao,

194
00:11:53,510 --> 00:11:54,840
it's totally our fault.

195
00:11:55,120 --> 00:11:56,980
You sure know traffic rules well.

196
00:11:58,120 --> 00:11:59,000
You two jerks,

197
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:00,000
get out of the car!

198
00:12:02,360 --> 00:12:03,160
Are you crazy?

199
00:12:04,720 --> 00:12:05,720
You stay in the car.

200
00:12:05,720 --> 00:12:06,440
Don't get out.

201
00:12:06,440 --> 00:12:07,030
Be good.

202
00:12:07,270 --> 00:12:08,390
Get the hell out!

203
00:12:16,480 --> 00:12:17,480
Sir, are you okay?

204
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:19,270
Here, Mr. Green Hat,

205
00:12:19,270 --> 00:12:20,000
have a smoke and calm down.

206
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:20,870
Okay my ass!

207
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:22,630
Look at how you smashed my car.

208
00:12:22,630 --> 00:12:23,840
Cut the crap. Pay up.

209
00:12:24,510 --> 00:12:25,080
Pay up?

210
00:12:25,960 --> 00:12:26,720
Sir, look,

211
00:12:26,720 --> 00:12:28,520
you've been brake-checking us all the way.

212
00:12:28,520 --> 00:12:29,000
Damn,

213
00:12:29,030 --> 00:12:30,690
you have the nerve to say that?

214
00:12:30,790 --> 00:12:32,480
I honked all the way for you to stop.

215
00:12:32,480 --> 00:12:33,360
Are you deaf?

216
00:12:33,550 --> 00:12:34,080
Besides,

217
00:12:34,080 --> 00:12:34,910
if that jerk in your car

218
00:12:34,910 --> 00:12:36,200
hadn't spit at me,

219
00:12:36,320 --> 00:12:37,120
why would I cut you off?

220
00:12:37,120 --> 00:12:38,510
Sir, let's keep things separate.

221
00:12:38,510 --> 00:12:40,200
The rear-end is your fault
for cutting me off,

222
00:12:40,200 --> 00:12:42,240
and the spitting is my buddy's fault.

223
00:12:42,240 --> 00:12:43,270
The end result is that both cars

224
00:12:43,270 --> 00:12:44,030
are damaged.

225
00:12:44,480 --> 00:12:46,080
I suggest we each fix our own.

226
00:12:47,240 --> 00:12:47,970
Cut the crap.

227
00:12:48,150 --> 00:12:48,630
Pay up.

228
00:12:49,960 --> 00:12:50,480
Go back.

229
00:12:59,600 --> 00:13:01,260
It's just about money, right?

230
00:13:01,510 --> 00:13:02,120
I only have

231
00:13:02,200 --> 00:13:03,480
3,000 here. Take it all.

232
00:13:03,480 --> 00:13:04,490
I have some small change too.

233
00:13:04,490 --> 00:13:04,870
No.

234
00:13:04,910 --> 00:13:06,030
I'll give it all to you, okay?

235
00:13:06,030 --> 00:13:06,440
No,

236
00:13:06,750 --> 00:13:08,440
you smashed my car like this,

237
00:13:08,630 --> 00:13:10,030
and you're offering 3,000?

238
00:13:10,030 --> 00:13:11,240
To fully repair this car,

239
00:13:11,240 --> 00:13:12,770
it'll cost at least 30,000!

240
00:13:14,720 --> 00:13:16,520
Sir, look at the car I'm driving.

241
00:13:16,550 --> 00:13:18,080
Do I look like I have 30,000?

242
00:13:22,630 --> 00:13:23,030
Fine.

243
00:13:23,240 --> 00:13:23,630
Fine.

244
00:13:23,870 --> 00:13:24,730
I admit defeat.

245
00:13:25,030 --> 00:13:26,240
I'm not trying to extort you.

246
00:13:26,240 --> 00:13:27,960
Extorting you with this piece of junk
is pointless anyway.

247
00:13:27,960 --> 00:13:28,600
How about this?

248
00:13:28,600 --> 00:13:30,460
You call your insurance company,

249
00:13:30,480 --> 00:13:32,540
so you won't have to
pay out of pocket.

250
00:13:35,240 --> 00:13:36,710
To be honest with you,

251
00:13:37,200 --> 00:13:39,000
our car doesn't have insurance.

252
00:13:39,080 --> 00:13:40,270
Either you take the 3,000,

253
00:13:40,270 --> 00:13:41,360
or you take full responsibility

254
00:13:41,360 --> 00:13:43,220
and go to your insurance company.

255
00:13:44,790 --> 00:13:46,390
I take full responsibility?

256
00:13:47,910 --> 00:13:49,080
You hit my car

257
00:13:49,080 --> 00:13:51,030
and want me to take full responsibility?

258
00:13:51,030 --> 00:13:52,230
Is that what you mean?

259
00:13:54,960 --> 00:13:55,840
Then how about I just give you my car?

260
00:13:55,840 --> 00:13:56,640
Do you want it?

261
00:14:09,320 --> 00:14:09,790
Yes.

262
00:14:12,120 --> 00:14:15,680
[We are college students
who lost our money. Please help.]

263
00:14:15,710 --> 00:14:18,940
[Bless you kind people.]

264
00:14:19,360 --> 00:14:21,620
The market was better back in those days.

265
00:14:21,720 --> 00:14:23,030
Setting up an endgame on the overpass

266
00:14:23,030 --> 00:14:24,630
could earn me hundreds a day.

267
00:14:24,910 --> 00:14:25,970
What's an endgame?

268
00:14:26,840 --> 00:14:27,570
Have a heart.

269
00:14:28,870 --> 00:14:29,550
Chess.

270
00:14:31,150 --> 00:14:33,410
You don't understand that stuff anyway.

271
00:14:33,910 --> 00:14:35,780
We don't look like college students,
do we?

272
00:14:35,780 --> 00:14:36,710
What do you know?

273
00:14:36,920 --> 00:14:38,250
[We are college students
who lost our money. Please help.]

274
00:14:37,270 --> 00:14:38,130
Have some pity.

275
00:14:38,270 --> 00:14:39,430
[Bless you kind people.]

276
00:14:39,390 --> 00:14:40,630
That Professor Fu

277
00:14:40,630 --> 00:14:41,720
from Jingda University's math department

278
00:14:41,720 --> 00:14:42,580
is just like us.

279
00:14:43,390 --> 00:14:44,190
That unlucky?

280
00:14:46,360 --> 00:14:47,090
Ridiculous.

281
00:14:49,080 --> 00:14:50,270
Is there any food at home?

282
00:14:50,270 --> 00:14:52,000
There are some digestion pills.

283
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:53,130
Don't mention that.

284
00:14:56,270 --> 00:14:57,120
Have a heart.

285
00:14:57,150 --> 00:14:58,240
Give us eight bucks.

286
00:14:58,240 --> 00:14:58,670
Is there

287
00:14:58,670 --> 00:14:59,600
a junkyard nearby?

288
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:00,150
Give us eight bucks

289
00:15:00,150 --> 00:15:01,550
and we'll take you there.

290
00:15:01,910 --> 00:15:02,510
Then we...

291
00:15:05,360 --> 00:15:06,320
Where you think you going?

292
00:15:06,320 --> 00:15:07,150
Where you think you going?

293
00:15:07,150 --> 00:15:07,600
What?

294
00:15:07,630 --> 00:15:09,000
Honghong, Maomao or whatever.

295
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:10,090
Hong... Hongwei.

296
00:15:10,240 --> 00:15:10,790
Hongwei.

297
00:15:10,870 --> 00:15:11,930
What are you doing?

298
00:15:12,360 --> 00:15:12,840
What?

299
00:15:13,270 --> 00:15:13,930
Who are you?

300
00:15:15,080 --> 00:15:16,870
He owes me money. I'm collecting debt.

301
00:15:16,870 --> 00:15:17,080
Hey,

302
00:15:17,080 --> 00:15:18,120
if he owes money, talk about the money.

303
00:15:18,120 --> 00:15:19,600
Why are you getting physical?

304
00:15:19,600 --> 00:15:20,150
So what?

305
00:15:20,670 --> 00:15:22,000
How much does he owe you?

306
00:15:22,030 --> 00:15:23,160
A hundred thousand.

307
00:15:24,630 --> 00:15:25,550
A hundred thousand?

308
00:15:25,550 --> 00:15:25,840
Wait.

309
00:15:25,840 --> 00:15:26,630
You're asking people like us

310
00:15:26,630 --> 00:15:27,360
for 100,000?

311
00:15:27,790 --> 00:15:29,450
Are you broke out of your mind?

312
00:15:30,510 --> 00:15:31,240
What is this?

313
00:15:31,310 --> 00:15:32,610
[IOU]

314
00:15:37,270 --> 00:15:38,130
You wrote this?

315
00:15:39,310 --> 00:15:40,040
I wrote this.

316
00:15:42,780 --> 00:15:45,120
-Don't have that much money.
-Don't have that much money.

317
00:15:45,120 --> 00:15:45,880
No money?

318
00:15:46,320 --> 00:15:47,320
Don't you have a junkyard?

319
00:15:47,320 --> 00:15:48,200
Use that to pay the debt.

320
00:15:48,200 --> 00:15:48,480
No,

321
00:15:48,510 --> 00:15:49,440
that junkyard

322
00:15:49,440 --> 00:15:50,390
-It's his.
-It’s mine.

323
00:15:50,390 --> 00:15:50,910
Right.

324
00:15:51,090 --> 00:15:51,490
Well,

325
00:15:51,720 --> 00:15:52,720
how can you use my junkyard

326
00:15:52,720 --> 00:15:53,580
to pay his debt?

327
00:15:53,600 --> 00:15:54,240
Why not?

328
00:15:54,840 --> 00:15:56,000
That's not reasonable.

329
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:57,430
Do I look like a reasonable person?

330
00:15:57,430 --> 00:15:59,090
He's not a reasonable person.

331
00:15:59,440 --> 00:16:00,100
Hey, you...

332
00:16:01,150 --> 00:16:02,190
How about this?

333
00:16:02,390 --> 00:16:03,600
You just strangle him,

334
00:16:03,600 --> 00:16:04,830
and won't the debt be written off?

335
00:16:04,830 --> 00:16:06,630
-Sir, don’t.
-Can you be reasonable?

336
00:16:06,630 --> 00:16:07,720
How am I not reasonable?

337
00:16:07,720 --> 00:16:08,390
If I strangle him,

338
00:16:08,390 --> 00:16:09,440
wouldn't you still have to pay the debt?

339
00:16:09,440 --> 00:16:10,120
Right, then wouldn't it still be...

340
00:16:10,120 --> 00:16:11,120
Why should I pay the debt?

341
00:16:11,120 --> 00:16:11,600
Why?

342
00:16:11,720 --> 00:16:12,480
Why?

343
00:16:14,790 --> 00:16:15,390
Why?

344
00:16:15,390 --> 00:16:16,520
No, there's a knife.

345
00:16:16,550 --> 00:16:17,080
No, no.

346
00:16:17,240 --> 00:16:17,840
No need.

347
00:16:17,870 --> 00:16:18,510
No need, sir.

348
00:16:18,510 --> 00:16:19,320
No, no need to show it.

349
00:16:19,320 --> 00:16:20,030
-No need to show it.
-Thank you.

350
00:16:20,030 --> 00:16:20,550
I appreciate the thought.

351
00:16:20,550 --> 00:16:21,950
Thanks for your trouble.

352
00:16:22,910 --> 00:16:23,440
Well...

353
00:16:24,600 --> 00:16:25,030
So...

354
00:16:26,390 --> 00:16:27,590
There's an IOU.

355
00:16:27,960 --> 00:16:29,690
The money was borrowed, right?

356
00:16:32,150 --> 00:16:33,410
A hundred thousand...

357
00:16:33,750 --> 00:16:35,200
Give me a week.

358
00:16:35,910 --> 00:16:37,840
I'll pay you back 100,000 in a week.

359
00:16:38,790 --> 00:16:39,590
Is a week okay?

360
00:16:39,910 --> 00:16:40,320
Okay.

361
00:16:41,120 --> 00:16:41,720
One week.

362
00:16:45,960 --> 00:16:47,550
Is there any place nearby
that sells zipper oil?

363
00:16:47,550 --> 00:16:48,750
Over there, up there.

364
00:16:48,910 --> 00:16:49,510
Turn left.

365
00:16:50,320 --> 00:16:50,840
Why?

366
00:16:56,960 --> 00:16:58,390
You talked too fast.

367
00:16:59,390 --> 00:17:00,510
You promised him a week.

368
00:17:00,510 --> 00:17:01,000
Can you get 100,000

369
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:02,080
in a week?

370
00:17:02,480 --> 00:17:03,720
Anyway, I don't have it.

371
00:17:03,720 --> 00:17:04,200
What?

372
00:17:04,349 --> 00:17:06,310
Do you think money grows on trees?

373
00:17:06,790 --> 00:17:07,589
No, Tinggang!

374
00:17:07,680 --> 00:17:08,790
Don't!

375
00:17:08,790 --> 00:17:10,390
How dare you borrow 100,000?

376
00:17:10,440 --> 00:17:11,040
Tinggang.

377
00:17:11,310 --> 00:17:12,240
It's Li Penggai.

378
00:17:12,240 --> 00:17:13,710
Li Penggai extorted me.

379
00:17:14,069 --> 00:17:14,750
Li Penggai?

380
00:17:14,790 --> 00:17:15,310
Yes.

381
00:17:15,510 --> 00:17:16,230
Li Penggai said

382
00:17:16,230 --> 00:17:17,349
as long as he got the 100,000,

383
00:17:17,349 --> 00:17:19,079
he wouldn't give us a hard time.

384
00:17:20,730 --> 00:17:22,440
He wouldn't give you a hard time!

385
00:17:22,440 --> 00:17:24,099
What does it have to do with me?

386
00:17:24,109 --> 00:17:24,880
I...

387
00:17:24,930 --> 00:17:26,200
I just brought you in.

388
00:17:26,200 --> 00:17:27,530
You just joined, right?

389
00:17:28,030 --> 00:17:28,440
You...

390
00:17:28,960 --> 00:17:29,360
You...

391
00:17:29,510 --> 00:17:30,310
Don't, don't.

392
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:31,400
I...

393
00:17:35,350 --> 00:17:37,210
Where are we going to get 100,000?

394
00:17:40,270 --> 00:17:42,110
If we can't, let's pull off a big heist!

395
00:17:42,110 --> 00:17:42,830
How big?

396
00:17:45,070 --> 00:17:47,400
If we can't, let's pull off
a medium heist!

397
00:17:48,270 --> 00:17:49,240
Medium is fine.

398
00:18:12,510 --> 00:18:13,370
How about here?

399
00:18:13,960 --> 00:18:14,820
Is anyone here?

400
00:18:16,880 --> 00:18:17,750
Is anyone here?

401
00:18:19,110 --> 00:18:20,310
Is anyone here?

402
00:18:25,200 --> 00:18:26,720
Since we got to Sanjiangkou,

403
00:18:26,720 --> 00:18:27,750
this car has been with us.

404
00:18:27,750 --> 00:18:28,720
Now that we're selling it,

405
00:18:28,720 --> 00:18:30,120
I kind of miss it already.

406
00:18:30,640 --> 00:18:32,640
You got infected by that corrupt official.

407
00:18:32,640 --> 00:18:33,830
You're addicted to junk cars.

408
00:18:33,830 --> 00:18:34,880
Not exactly.

409
00:18:35,590 --> 00:18:36,920
We bought it for 25,000.

410
00:18:37,110 --> 00:18:39,310
Is it appropriate to sell it for 30,000?

411
00:18:41,720 --> 00:18:43,000
I'm thinking too small.

412
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:44,400
We'll sell it for 50,000.

413
00:18:46,270 --> 00:18:47,130
Is anyone here?

414
00:18:47,790 --> 00:18:48,850
Is anyone here?

415
00:18:48,920 --> 00:18:50,250
Alright, stop yelling.

416
00:18:51,070 --> 00:18:51,510
You know

417
00:18:51,510 --> 00:18:53,400
we bought this junk car for 25,000.

418
00:18:53,400 --> 00:18:55,330
But 20,000 went to fake documents.

419
00:18:55,720 --> 00:18:57,310
The car is only worth 5,000.

420
00:18:58,920 --> 00:19:01,520
So you mean we'll sell it
at the original price?

421
00:19:12,960 --> 00:19:13,270
No.

422
00:19:13,440 --> 00:19:15,300
We can't sell it by weight, right?

423
00:19:16,790 --> 00:19:18,400
You just mentioned thinking small.

424
00:19:18,400 --> 00:19:19,400
I reflected on it.

425
00:19:19,920 --> 00:19:21,880
We are going to pull off a big heist now.

426
00:19:21,880 --> 00:19:23,200
Can we haggle over

427
00:19:23,200 --> 00:19:24,310
this petty cash?

428
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:26,400
What if this car

429
00:19:26,440 --> 00:19:27,840
exposes our whereabouts

430
00:19:28,160 --> 00:19:29,420
and alerts the police?

431
00:19:29,880 --> 00:19:31,610
How can we do great things then?

432
00:19:32,430 --> 00:19:33,430
Then what do we do?

433
00:19:35,110 --> 00:19:36,510
We'll give the car away.

434
00:19:36,720 --> 00:19:37,450
Give it away?

435
00:19:37,750 --> 00:19:38,400
To whom?

436
00:19:38,590 --> 00:19:39,720
There's no one here.

437
00:19:40,070 --> 00:19:41,640
Because there is no one here,

438
00:19:41,640 --> 00:19:42,960
no one will see us.

439
00:19:44,750 --> 00:19:46,150
We'll just leave it here.

440
00:19:59,830 --> 00:20:01,430
First time doing a good deed.

441
00:20:01,510 --> 00:20:03,440
I'll leave a note for the lucky one.

442
00:20:14,550 --> 00:20:15,350
Stop shaking!

443
00:20:15,790 --> 00:20:16,440
If you break

444
00:20:16,440 --> 00:20:17,160
my new car's suspension,

445
00:20:17,160 --> 00:20:18,070
I'll kill you.

446
00:20:22,030 --> 00:20:23,090
Can you rob houses?

447
00:20:25,920 --> 00:20:27,720
Can you murder and commit arson?

448
00:20:29,310 --> 00:20:30,350
Can you commit petty theft?

449
00:20:30,350 --> 00:20:31,080
I can do that.

450
00:20:31,590 --> 00:20:32,430
No, you can't!

451
00:20:32,430 --> 00:20:34,270
You don't even dare to steal a bicycle.

452
00:20:34,270 --> 00:20:35,200
For that 100,000,

453
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:36,800
we have to steal a car, got it?

454
00:20:38,510 --> 00:20:38,920
Bro.

455
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:39,880
Don't call me bro.

456
00:20:39,880 --> 00:20:41,080
There really is a car.

457
00:20:43,110 --> 00:20:45,170
Even if there is a car, it's not yours.

458
00:20:45,480 --> 00:20:46,480
Whose car is this?

459
00:20:47,270 --> 00:20:48,310
Who parked their car here?

460
00:20:48,310 --> 00:20:49,440
You can't park here!

461
00:20:50,350 --> 00:20:51,310
Who parked here?

462
00:20:51,880 --> 00:20:52,590
For...

463
00:20:53,720 --> 00:20:54,110
free.

464
00:20:54,110 --> 00:20:55,160
F-for free?

465
00:20:55,510 --> 00:20:56,240
For free?

466
00:20:56,400 --> 00:20:56,880
In your dreams.

467
00:20:56,880 --> 00:20:57,640
No, look.

468
00:20:58,480 --> 00:20:59,070
Impossible.

469
00:20:59,070 --> 00:20:59,510
Look.

470
00:20:59,950 --> 00:21:02,900
♪ The stars twinkle, the moon curves ♪

471
00:21:00,040 --> 00:21:03,890
[For free]

472
00:21:00,720 --> 00:21:01,270
Look.

473
00:21:01,480 --> 00:21:02,920
I recognize these two words.

474
00:21:02,920 --> 00:21:03,790
It's for free.

475
00:21:05,750 --> 00:21:06,750
Isn't it for free?

476
00:21:06,900 --> 00:21:11,520
♪ A gentle breeze
sways the willow branches ♪

477
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:09,660
The car door opens too.

478
00:21:18,200 --> 00:21:19,310
Heaven blessed us?

479
00:21:22,920 --> 00:21:24,850
And it comes with half a tank of gas.

480
00:21:32,000 --> 00:21:33,260
Will this leave a scar?

481
00:21:33,830 --> 00:21:34,920
It's a very small cut.

482
00:21:34,920 --> 00:21:36,180
Don't worry, it won't.

483
00:21:38,160 --> 00:21:38,900
Song Xing,

484
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:40,460
you are really something.

485
00:21:40,590 --> 00:21:42,790
You acted recklessly
and got Li Qian injured.

486
00:21:42,790 --> 00:21:43,880
If something really went wrong,

487
00:21:43,880 --> 00:21:45,480
could you take the responsibility?

488
00:21:45,480 --> 00:21:46,540
Stop scolding him.

489
00:21:49,680 --> 00:21:51,210
Chief Zhang, Captain Wang.

490
00:21:51,960 --> 00:21:53,400
There's nothing I can do either.

491
00:21:53,400 --> 00:21:54,750
We can't control this matter.

492
00:21:54,750 --> 00:21:55,640
If word gets out...

493
00:21:55,640 --> 00:21:56,700
Yes, I know, I know.

494
00:21:57,640 --> 00:21:58,570
Why are you here?

495
00:21:58,750 --> 00:22:00,640
You should rest for a couple of days.

496
00:22:00,640 --> 00:22:02,030
It's too stuffy in the dorm.

497
00:22:02,030 --> 00:22:02,920
Please let me work.

498
00:22:02,920 --> 00:22:04,550
No, you'd better not join for now.

499
00:22:04,550 --> 00:22:05,960
If I let you work while injured again,

500
00:22:05,960 --> 00:22:07,890
Director Gao will punish me again.

501
00:22:11,550 --> 00:22:12,480
I'll punish him.

502
00:22:14,600 --> 00:22:16,130
Li Qian, come here.

503
00:22:20,010 --> 00:22:20,720
Come.

504
00:22:21,310 --> 00:22:21,970
Stand here.

505
00:22:22,640 --> 00:22:23,440
Get over here.

506
00:22:28,400 --> 00:22:30,260
Do you know why the chief is angry?

507
00:22:31,880 --> 00:22:33,590
Because I publicly pointed out

508
00:22:33,590 --> 00:22:34,400
that he misread a word.

509
00:22:34,400 --> 00:22:35,240
Cut the crap.

510
00:22:36,070 --> 00:22:37,730
Would the chief be this petty?

511
00:22:41,480 --> 00:22:43,480
I'm telling you, listen carefully.

512
00:22:43,510 --> 00:22:44,520
It's because

513
00:22:44,920 --> 00:22:46,070
the girl got hurt.

514
00:22:47,590 --> 00:22:50,250
Song Xing, you're considered
a veteran, right?

515
00:22:50,440 --> 00:22:51,770
Li Qian is just a rookie.

516
00:22:52,000 --> 00:22:53,460
When things happen to you,

517
00:22:53,790 --> 00:22:55,590
you're impulsive and reckless.

518
00:22:55,680 --> 00:22:56,880
When things happen to Li Qian,

519
00:22:56,880 --> 00:22:58,240
she's calm and collected.

520
00:22:58,240 --> 00:22:59,590
You call yourself an investigator,

521
00:22:59,590 --> 00:23:00,750
yet you got locked in an elevator.

522
00:23:00,750 --> 00:23:01,480
If word gets out,

523
00:23:01,480 --> 00:23:02,510
you'll become a laughingstock.

524
00:23:02,510 --> 00:23:02,960
Right?

525
00:23:04,440 --> 00:23:05,100
Li Qian here

526
00:23:05,510 --> 00:23:07,240
outsmarted ruthless bandits.

527
00:23:07,550 --> 00:23:08,480
If word gets out,

528
00:23:08,680 --> 00:23:10,440
everyone will give her a thumbs up.

529
00:23:10,440 --> 00:23:11,770
Don't you feel ashamed?

530
00:23:15,720 --> 00:23:16,380
I was wrong.

531
00:23:16,680 --> 00:23:17,540
You were wrong.

532
00:23:18,310 --> 00:23:19,960
As for the future work of the task force,

533
00:23:19,960 --> 00:23:21,760
don't participate in it for now.

534
00:23:21,830 --> 00:23:22,890
Don't do this, I...

535
00:23:23,480 --> 00:23:24,240
C-Chief.

536
00:23:24,270 --> 00:23:24,590
I...

537
00:23:24,750 --> 00:23:25,830
I urgently need a chance now

538
00:23:25,830 --> 00:23:26,760
to prove myself.

539
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:27,590
If Captain Wang doesn't let me

540
00:23:27,590 --> 00:23:28,640
participate in the investigation,

541
00:23:28,640 --> 00:23:29,160
then won't I really become

542
00:23:29,160 --> 00:23:30,420
the joke of the bureau?

543
00:23:30,750 --> 00:23:31,880
You already are the personification

544
00:23:31,880 --> 00:23:32,880
of a joke.

545
00:23:33,400 --> 00:23:33,800
You...

546
00:23:36,310 --> 00:23:37,720
Then what should I do?

547
00:23:38,200 --> 00:23:38,720
You...

548
00:23:38,880 --> 00:23:40,680
You can make up for your mistakes

549
00:23:41,030 --> 00:23:42,240
by taking care of the injured.

550
00:23:42,240 --> 00:23:43,840
When Li Qian's injury heals,

551
00:23:44,110 --> 00:23:45,770
we'll talk about your matter.

552
00:23:49,510 --> 00:23:50,110
Let's start the meeting.

553
00:23:50,110 --> 00:23:50,480
Okay.

554
00:23:52,400 --> 00:23:53,660
Come on, meeting time.

555
00:24:07,880 --> 00:24:08,540
Let me do it.

556
00:24:10,590 --> 00:24:13,120
Are you really
taking care of me exclusively?

557
00:24:14,160 --> 00:24:15,220
I'm sorry, Li Qian.

558
00:24:17,350 --> 00:24:19,160
These days, I'm so unlucky
cold water gets stuck in my teeth.

559
00:24:19,160 --> 00:24:21,020
Let's just wait for the hot water.

560
00:24:26,030 --> 00:24:27,830
That crappy elevator
at Zheng Yongbing's place...

561
00:24:27,830 --> 00:24:28,690
Did I blame you?

562
00:24:31,020 --> 00:24:31,470
No.

563
00:24:31,750 --> 00:24:32,830
I blame myself.

564
00:24:33,270 --> 00:24:34,790
Blaming yourself is useless now.

565
00:24:34,790 --> 00:24:35,750
We need to find a way

566
00:24:35,750 --> 00:24:37,350
to get back to the task force.

567
00:24:37,720 --> 00:24:39,480
That's why I'm here to take care of you.

568
00:24:39,480 --> 00:24:40,590
Your injury needs to heal quickly

569
00:24:40,590 --> 00:24:41,850
for us to have any hope.

570
00:24:45,030 --> 00:24:46,240
Did you really not find anything

571
00:24:46,240 --> 00:24:47,770
at Zheng Yongbing's place?

572
00:24:48,070 --> 00:24:49,000
I found nothing.

573
00:24:49,510 --> 00:24:51,170
There are photos of the scene.

574
00:25:08,200 --> 00:25:09,680
Then did you check Ye Jian's

575
00:25:09,680 --> 00:25:10,280
computer,

576
00:25:10,720 --> 00:25:11,310
phone,

577
00:25:11,440 --> 00:25:12,680
apps, WeChat,

578
00:25:13,160 --> 00:25:15,370
and other electronics?

579
00:25:15,550 --> 00:25:17,270
We've finished this part too.

580
00:25:17,440 --> 00:25:18,790
Before Captain Ye left,

581
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:18,960
[Buy now] [Add to cart]

582
